18/07/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- A Bosnian Muslim was sentenced to 30 years in prison for war crimes against Serbs during the 1992-1995 conflict.
The country's special war crimes chamber on Tuesday (July 17th) found Niset Ramic guilty of murdering four Serb civilians and injuring two others in a village near Visoko in June 1992, while he was a member of the Visoko Territorial Defence Force He is already serving a 20-year sentence for murder and robbery.
Both terms will run concurrently.
(Reuters, AFP, PBS BiH, DPA - 17/07/07)
